 Holy Mother, Ma Sarada, came ac=\r\nross some nice quotations:\n=C2=A0\n\nOrdinary human love results in misery. L=\r\nove for God brings blessedness.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nAs you progress in your spiritual =\r\npractice you will see the same Being in you as in me, and that He is in all=\r\n men, be they of the lowest castes. Then you will acquire humility.\n=C2=A0\n=\r\n\n\nIn course of time one does not feel even the existence of God. After atta=\r\nining enlightenment one sees that Gods and deities are all maya. Everything=\r\n comes into existence in time and disappears in time. Gods and such things =\r\nreally disappear at the dawn of enlightenment. The aspirant then realizes t=\r\nhat the Mother alone pervades the universe. All then become one.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nW=\r\nhere is that competent student who can understand spiritual instruction? Fi=\r\nrst of all one should be fit; otherwise the instructions prove futile.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\n\n\nAll great spiritual=C2=A0teachers are one. The same power of God work=\r\ns through them all.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nFrom time immemorial so many people have pract=\r\nised image-worship and thereby got liberation. Who says it=C2=A0is nothing?=\r\n\n=C2=A0\n\n\nGod is one.s very own. One realizes him in proportion to the inte=\r\nnsity of one&#39;s feeling for him.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nWhat does a man become by realizin=\r\ng God? Does he grow two horns? No, what happens is , he develops discrimina=\r\ntion between the real and the unreal, becomes conscious spiritually, and go=\r\nes beyond life and death. God is realized in spirit. How else can one see G=\r\nod? Has God talked to anyone who is devoid of ecstatic fervour? One sees Go=\r\nd in spiritual vision, talks to him, and establishes relationship with him =\r\nin spirit.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nThrough these spiritual disciplines the ties of past ka=\r\nrma are cut asunder. But the realization of God cannot be achieved without =\r\necstatic love for him.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nEven the impossible becomes possible throug=\r\nh devotion.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nNeither mantra nor scripture is of any avail; bhakti o=\r\nr devotion alone accomplishes everything.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nEven the wise could hard=\r\nly realize the natureof Brahman by argument. Is Brahman an object of discus=\r\nsion?\n=C2=A0\n\n\nGive up this dry discussion, this hodgepodge of philosophy. =\r\nWho has been able to know God by reasoning?\n=C2=A0\n\n\nOne.s love of God depe=\r\nnds entirely upon one.s inner feeling. Love of God is the essential thing.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\n\n\nHave intense devotion to God. One must work hard. How can one achi=\r\neve anything without effort? You must devote some time for prayer even in t=\r\nhe midst of the busiest hour of the day.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nGod cannot be realized wi=\r\nthout love, yes, sincere, absolute=C2=A0love.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nAll depends on the g=\r\nrace of God. He bestows his grace upon anyone he likes. Grace is the import=\r\nant thing.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nThe human teacher utters the mantra into the ear; but G=\r\nod breathes the spirit into the soul.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nThe grace of God is the thin=\r\ng that is needful.One should pray for the grace of God. One must pray sitti=\r\nng on the bank of the river. One will be taken across in proper time.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\n\n\nEven the water which has got a natural tendency to flow downwards, is=\r\n drawn up to the sky by the sun.s rays. In the same way, God.s grace lifts =\r\nup the mind which has got a tendency to run after sense objects.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nO=\r\nne must perform work. It is only through work that the bondage of work will=\r\n be cut asunder and one will acquire a spirit of non-attachment. One should=\r\n not be without work even for a moment.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nIf you do not pray to God,=\r\n what is that to him? It is only your misfortune.\n=C2=A0\n\n\nEverything depen=\r\nds upon one.s mind. Nothing can be achieved without purity of mind.\n=C2=A0\n=\r\n\n\nIt is said, .The aspirant might have received the grace of the guru, the =\r\nLord and his devotees; but he comes to grief without the grace of .one... T=\r\nhat .one. is the mind. The mind of the aspirant must be gracious to him.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\n\n&quot;Between me and You, there is only me.\nTa=\r\nke away the me, so only You remain&quot; - Hallaj\n\n--- On Sat, 24/4/10, chaudhur=\r\ni.krishnendu &lt;krishnenduchdhr@...&gt; wrote:\n\n\nFrom: chaudhuri.krishnend=\r\nu &lt;krishnenduchdhr@...&gt;\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Mantra Japa\nTo: v=\r\nedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\nDate: Saturday, 24 April, 2010, 1:12 AM\n\n\n=C2=\r\n=A0 \n\n\n\nRegarding Japam go tthrough a book Japa yoga by Swami Shivananda.An=\r\n excellent book and it costs too little.\nYou will get all the PRACTICAL ins=\r\ntructions if you are planning to move in this path.\n\n--- In vedic-wisdom@ y=\r\nahoogroups. com, Nagraj Kota &lt;nagraj_um@. ..&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Dear Narasimhagaru=\r\n, \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt; I apologise for taking freedom in repeating my prior qu=\r\nestions that I posted a couple of times on the forum before. But since you =\r\nare responding again, I am hoping that you would catch them now. \n&gt; =C3=82=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt; 1. Is there a specific Homam prescribed for Gayatri Mata or can we=\r\n just use avahana mantra &#39;OmityEkAkshara Brahma&#39; of Sandhyavandanam and pro=\r\nceed? \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt; 2. Is there one for Lord Karthikeya?\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0=\r\n\n&gt; Nagraj Kota\n&gt; \n&gt; --- On Wed, 4/21/10, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote:=\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; From: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;\n&gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Ma=\r\nntra Japa\n&gt; To: vedic-wisdom@ yahoogroups. com\n&gt; Cc: &quot;Veneet Kumar&quot; &lt;kvenee=\r\nt@... &gt;\n&gt; Date: Wednesday, April 21, 2010, 5:37 PM\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0 \n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; Namaste Veneet ji,\n&gt; \n&gt; Nice questions! You can find some answers =\r\nin the archives. I will briefly answer again.\n&gt; \n&gt; On your first point: Yes=\r\n, Lord Krishna did indeed say in the 10th chapter of BhagavadGita: &quot;yaGYaan=\r\naam japayaGYo.asmi&quot; (of all sacrifices/rituals, I am the japa yajna, i.e. c=\r\nhanting of mantras).\n&gt; \n&gt; * * *\n&gt; \n&gt; We can get it in right perspective by =\r\nnoting that the very previous line says &quot;I am Om among all mantras&quot;.\n&gt; \n&gt; Y=\r\nes, Om represents the pure and absolute essence of universe. However, is it=\r\n possible for everyone to meditate just using &quot;Om&quot; and reach god? Probably =\r\nnot. Are Krishna devotees leaving other mantras such as the mahamantra (Har=\r\ne krishna mantra) and doing japam only with &quot;Om&quot;, because Krishna said I am=\r\n &quot;Om&quot; among mantras? Of course, not.\n&gt; \n&gt; Same thing holds to japam vs othe=\r\nr sadhanas such as homam.\n&gt; \n&gt; Just as one may need ropes and other gear to=\r\n climb mount everest, one may need to employ mantras other than &quot;Om&quot; and pr=\r\nactices other than &quot;japam&quot; to overcome one&#39;s short-comings and reach the su=\r\nmmit of the absolute, represented by Om (and all other things mentioned by =\r\nKrishna).\n&gt; \n&gt; * * *\n&gt; \n&gt; When you do an external sacrifical ritual such as=\r\n homam, your body is engaging in actions. So your mind has to be attached t=\r\no the body and use it in a particular way. Can one reach samadhi while doin=\r\ng homam? Unlikely. One is more likely to reach samadhi when one stops the e=\r\nxternal actions. Mind may be withdrawn completely from the body and absorb =\r\nfully in the mantra at some stage then.\n&gt; \n&gt; From the point of view, japam =\r\n(sitting still and meditating on a mantra) is the ultimate sadhana.\n&gt; \n&gt; Ho=\r\nwever, not everyone can reach god like that. There are so many vasanas (con=\r\nditioning) in the mind that needs to be purged/purified slowly. Until that =\r\nis done, japam may not help one reach god. Until then, taking the help of a=\r\nn external pure object (such as fire) that has a purifying effect on one&#39;s =\r\nsubtle consciousness can be helpful. It *prepares* one for good japam.\n&gt; \n&gt;=\r\n * * *\n&gt; \n&gt; A lot of priests do homam and then leave the fire and go away. =\r\nIn the homam manuals, I have made it a point to insist that people do japam=\r\n with their favorite mantra at the end of the homam, while sitting still wi=\r\nth closed eyes. The idea is that homam purifies subtle consciousness and *p=\r\nrepares* one for reaching god, while it is finally japam that takes one to =\r\ngod. After every homam, one&#39;s internal purity is at a maximum (a local maxi=\r\nmum, temporally speaking - sorry for the technical jargon) and japam will b=\r\ne more fruitful than at other times.\n&gt; \n&gt; * * *\n&gt; \n&gt; Now onto other questio=\r\nns:\n&gt; \n&gt; (1) It is unfruitful in the sense that it does not take you closer=\r\n to god. It is fruitful in the sense that it stops you from going much furt=\r\nher away from god. After all, if you weren&#39;t engaged in that japam and you =\r\nwere doing some other activity, probably your mind will wander even more.\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; I suggest looking at disturbing thoughts in the middle of a japam as a =\r\nheckler interrupting your speech. Instead of arguing and fighting with the =\r\nheckler, simply take note of him, pause for a second and move on. Instead o=\r\nf panicking or worrying, simply take note of your thoughts, pause for a sec=\r\nond and move on.\n&gt; \n&gt; (2) Mantra means that which protects (tra) the mind (=\r\nmana). Various vasanas (conditioning) are pulling the mind in different dir=\r\nections to react to various situations in various ways and that activity ti=\r\nres out the mind. You protect it by anchoring it in a mantra and teaching i=\r\nt to overcome the pulls of vasana.\n&gt; \n&gt; The proof of whether a mantra or ja=\r\npam or homam is working for you or not is whether there is a slow internal =\r\ntransformation in you or not, whether your internal reaction to various ext=\r\nernal things is changing for the better or not.\n&gt; \n&gt; (3) Difficult. This is=\r\n where a good guru is helpful.\n&gt; \n&gt; Actually, in this age, technical perfec=\r\ntion is almost ruled out. I suggest doing whatever one does with a sense of=\r\n surrender and humility. If there is something partly correct that somebody=\r\n is doing, it will slowly increase with time and Nature will remove imperfe=\r\nctions with time.\n&gt; \n&gt; (4) I can write Obama&#39;s name and Gordon&#39;s name on sh=\r\neets of paper next to me and pretend that they came there and sat there. Wi=\r\nll they really do it? On the other hand, if I am a world leader holding a s=\r\nummit, probably I can make them actually come and sit there.\n&gt; \n&gt; Nyasa mea=\r\nns placement. When you do nyasa, you place various vibrations (sound patter=\r\nns) or energies (deities) in various body parts. For most of us with distra=\r\ncted minds, it is merely a formality and means nothing. Only a sadhaka with=\r\n a pure, pointed and focused mind can actually place various vibrations and=\r\n energies in various body parts.\n&gt; \n&gt; I always suggest to people to do nyas=\r\na as taught by elders (so that the knowledge lives and is passed on), but n=\r\not worry too much about it.\n&gt; \n&gt; As I said, we are in the midst of deepenin=\r\ng Kali and the level of sadhakas is not as high as in the old days. Technic=\r\nal perfection will become rarer and rarer. It is better to focus on surrend=\r\ner and humility.\n&gt; \n&gt; Best regards,\n&gt; Narasimha\n&gt; ------------ --------- --=\r\n------- --------- --------- --------- -\n&gt; Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyoti=\r\nsh Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short H=\r\nomam and Pitri Tarpana:\n&gt; http://www.VedicAst rologer.org\n&gt; Films that make=\r\n a difference: http://SaraswatiFil ms.org\n&gt; Spirituality: http://group